cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.IR

The paper deals with recognizing activities from images captured by wearable cameras, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) for classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The health applications of recognizing activities of daily living suggest that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of wearable cameras suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of contextual information from a fully connected layer suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
